Responsibilities:
Work independently within the assigned account and grow Valves business.
Provide sales forecast and achieve / exceed bookings, sales and profitability targets set for the business unit business in Singapore.
Tap on prospects, analyze requirements to develop winning strategies and negotiate to win the business profitably.
Maintain excellent account management skills and build strong relationships with external customers and internal service team.
Co-ordinate with sales support team to generate quotes for order processing, project team, instrumentsâ€™ documentation and also buy-out item, if any.
Work closely with Business Unit Marketing team to plan and implement promotional seminars. In addition, to provide feedback and market input to the marketing team.
Participate in project pursuit for multi-division projects destination to Singapore.
Requirements:
Diploma / Degree in Engineering (Mechanical / Instrumentation / Chemical / Electrical) with 1 to 3 years of sales experience in the process control industry. Senior position will be offered to candidates with longer industry experience.
Knowledge in Control valves industry, commercial terms and conditions of sale will be an advantage.
Good in analytical and questioning skills coupled with ability to develop and implement strategies.
Strong interpersonal and communication skills and strong negotiation skills.